1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:17,567
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhodassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhodassa

2
00:00:18,155 --> 00:00:34,881
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambuddhassa Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-enlightened one.

3
00:00:34,901 --> 00:00:45,377
So, I want to finish the four Brahma-viharas, the dwelling place of the gods, the highest, they represent the highest mental states that we can develop.

4
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:55,606
also known as, remember, the illimitables, in the sense that there's no definable end, there's no definable quantity with which you can develop these things.

5
00:00:56,646 --> 00:00:58,088
It's as great as the mind is.

6
00:01:00,493 --> 00:01:01,954
So I want to finish with equanimity.

7
00:01:02,314 --> 00:01:08,543
So we've done compassion, love, and sympathetic joy.

8
00:01:08,563 --> 00:01:11,668
So now equanimity is...

9
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:23,611
Number four, and it's in a sense the most important, it's the highest quality of all really, the highest attitude that we can develop.

10
00:01:24,992 --> 00:01:27,194
First of all, let's just say how you establish it.

11
00:01:30,097 --> 00:01:34,423
I always think it's best to establish it in a standing posture, but you can do it anywhere really.

12
00:01:35,102 --> 00:01:40,608
First of all, to getting contact with the body, the sensations of the body.

13
00:01:40,724 --> 00:01:47,734
You can go up the body or down the body, it doesn't matter, but actually getting contact with the inner part of ourselves, the body, feelings.

14
00:01:48,716 --> 00:01:54,305
And then to, as it were, launch your attention outwards, become aware of everything around you, what you can hear, what you can see.

15
00:01:54,346 --> 00:01:59,935
And then to bring them together and recognize that it's all just one mass of sensations, you see.

16
00:02:00,055 --> 00:02:04,703
It's all one mass of perception, sensations, feelings.

17
00:02:04,722 --> 00:02:07,828
The dividing line is, it doesn't have to be so sharp.

18
00:02:08,921 --> 00:02:11,206
And then as it were, you just sink into that.

19
00:02:12,348 --> 00:02:13,471
And that's your present moment.

20
00:02:13,531 --> 00:02:14,513
That's what you know.

21
00:02:15,174 --> 00:02:16,056
Just sink into it.

22
00:02:17,579 --> 00:02:26,657
And in that state, by being completely present to the present moment, that in itself is the aim.

23
00:02:26,777 --> 00:02:29,562
So you're not trying to achieve anything beyond that.

24
00:02:29,864 --> 00:02:31,146
That's equanimity, you see.

25
00:02:31,426 --> 00:02:32,650
You're just with the present moment.

26
00:02:33,010 --> 00:02:34,133
Completely receptive.

27
00:02:34,914 --> 00:02:35,757
The body's still.

28
00:02:35,817 --> 00:02:36,658
The heart calm.

29
00:02:37,139 --> 00:02:38,883
Just for a moment the mind's silent.

30
00:02:39,283 --> 00:02:40,145
To a point anyway.

31
00:02:41,087 --> 00:02:43,774
And this attitude of just receiving.

32
00:02:44,776 --> 00:02:45,959
That's your basis really.

33
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:47,502
Openness.

34
00:02:48,493 --> 00:03:16,459
and to do that often you have to be a little courageous but I think we also have to understand that when we're like that you see our contact with reality inverted commas is not being distorted by emotional values or by concepts so it's a really sort of important practice to lay this ground of complete openness and

35
00:03:18,042 --> 00:03:28,491
you can see how that then is quite easy from that point of view, say in the sitting posture, to bring up the enquiry, to bring up that sense of curiosity.

36
00:03:30,108 --> 00:03:48,292
And because it's coming from the base of that equanimous openness, that receptivity, you see, then the curiosity is not being distorted by some sort of preconceived ideas, prejudices, emotional states.

37
00:03:53,217 --> 00:03:57,043
And in daily life, you see, just entering a room.

38
00:03:58,627 --> 00:04:00,912
You know, just for a moment, receiving the room, you see.

39
00:04:02,235 --> 00:04:08,750
When you enter a shop or a supermarket, just stand there for a moment and just sort of receive it, you see.

40
00:04:08,789 --> 00:04:13,741
Instead of always beelining in, just receive the fullness of it, the atmosphere, everything.

41
00:04:15,525 --> 00:04:18,170
When you enter into a house, you see, just get a feel of it.

42
00:04:20,648 --> 00:04:21,449
Same with people.

43
00:04:21,468 --> 00:04:27,459
You see, you meet somebody and there's always this rush towards them rather than just receiving them.

44
00:04:27,478 --> 00:04:28,360
It only takes a moment.

45
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:31,225
It's just you receive the fullness of them.

46
00:04:31,245 --> 00:04:41,019
And not only how they actually look and that, but just catch what they're giving you, you know.

47
00:04:43,226 --> 00:04:46,740
I walked out of the gate and Jim, who sold the house to us, was at the road.

48
00:04:47,483 --> 00:04:50,875
He was with his daughter, Liz, whom I know, and their two children.

49
00:04:51,276 --> 00:05:04,312
And as I came out, I looked up the road, you see, just stood there for a moment, before making up, and I could see there was a lot of negativity coming towards me.

50
00:05:04,673 --> 00:05:09,538
They were quite upset with me because I hadn't looked after the water, which they think has been our responsibility.

51
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:19,190
And it's just receiving that, you know, and then making sure it doesn't distort how you're going to receive them, you see.

52
00:05:19,237 --> 00:05:20,399
and it's just going to backfire.

53
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:23,023
I approached them very slowly.

54
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:29,730
See, I went towards them rather than expecting them to go towards me, and then just really had a conversation about the water.

55
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:41,043
But if you don't, I find that if you don't do that, you very quickly get caught up in other people's states, you know, and it begins to spiral.

56
00:05:43,521 --> 00:05:44,463
It's the same with a meeting.

57
00:05:44,603 --> 00:05:45,865
You know, you walk into a meeting.

58
00:05:46,064 --> 00:05:46,846
It's just for a moment.

59
00:05:46,865 --> 00:05:47,687
It only takes a moment.

60
00:05:48,026 --> 00:05:50,050
But it's to do with the attitude, you see.

61
00:05:51,531 --> 00:05:52,533
So it's the same with the country.

62
00:05:52,572 --> 00:05:53,793
It's easy to do with the country, isn't it?

63
00:05:53,814 --> 00:05:56,057
You walk to the top of the hill and you just open up.

64
00:05:56,317 --> 00:05:58,079
You know, you just receive the countryside.

65
00:05:58,098 --> 00:05:59,401
So we can do it in certain places.

66
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,423
But you can do it on the bus, on the train.

67
00:06:02,463 --> 00:06:04,487
See, driving a car and you stop at the lights.

68
00:06:04,867 --> 00:06:05,987
Just receive the situation.

69
00:06:06,348 --> 00:06:12,516
So it's this constant effort just to drop into the present moment as...

70
00:06:12,495 --> 00:06:41,119
as it's being received rather than as you want to receive it I think once we get into the habit of it you just get in the habit it just naturally happens of just looking just listening just feeling now the important thing from the conditioning point of view spiritual point of view is that of course

71
00:06:41,908 --> 00:06:47,278
We can see what mood we're in, because remember, it's not just receiving outside, it's receiving inside.

72
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:56,733
So you can catch the mood you're in, you can catch the attitude that's coming up, the irritation, specifically the negative ones, because you don't want to get embroiled in them.

73
00:06:57,535 --> 00:07:02,262
And just that moment of equanimity where you're standing apart from, see?

74
00:07:02,901 --> 00:07:10,552
allows you just to be able not to get involved in any negative state that is within us.

75
00:07:10,572 --> 00:07:13,156
And by doing that, you can always put it to the side, you see.

76
00:07:13,315 --> 00:07:14,396
That's not suppressing it.

77
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,360
Suppressing means that you don't want to see it.

78
00:07:16,821 --> 00:07:18,483
You do want to see it, but this isn't the time.

79
00:07:19,064 --> 00:07:20,105
It's a completely different attitude.

80
00:07:20,404 --> 00:07:23,829
You just put it to the side and then you raise the goodwill, you see.

81
00:07:25,396 --> 00:07:29,851
So that's important in terms of not getting caught up in old conditionings.

82
00:07:29,891 --> 00:07:33,403
And remember that the less we get caught up in old conditionings the more they're dying out.

83
00:07:34,187 --> 00:07:36,334
If you don't use them they just die out.

84
00:07:38,490 --> 00:08:03,384
and the other part is intention you see because if you are still you can see your intention coming and the great thing about seeing that is that you can see whether it's wholesome or not you've got just that little bit of space so an intention doesn't come up just just hijack you you know you find yourself murdering somebody heavens above so you have the by seeing an intention

85
00:08:03,365 --> 00:08:06,288
You've just got that moment whether you want to empower it or not.

86
00:08:06,629 --> 00:08:08,630
It just gives you that little bit of control.

87
00:08:08,711 --> 00:08:22,786
And that's how you get this feeling of being in control of your life and not being sort of, you know, taken by our emotional state and others, other people, you see.

88
00:08:22,807 --> 00:08:29,894
So it's developing a heart or a heart free of aversion and fear.

89
00:08:30,516 --> 00:09:00,371
not wanting to receive afraid of receiving and a mental state which is impartial it's not caught up in partiality in prejudice in liking or not liking and hopefully not in delusion because you're seeing your thoughts you can see the thoughts and just not getting caught up in them so you can see it's a sort of passive state of wisdom a passive state

90
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:14,648
and out of that passive state then something active arises you see and from a point of view of our life you know this allows us to

91
00:09:15,943 --> 00:09:21,253
Meet the vicissitudes of life with a little bit of the old equanimity, equanimity.

92
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:28,585
So the usual ones that's in the scriptures are gain and loss, honor and dishonor, happiness and misery, praise and blame.

93
00:09:28,644 --> 00:09:40,585
So if the good side comes, the gain, the honor, the happiness, the praise, you don't grab it, you don't sort of seep into it.

94
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:44,616
Everything that rises has to fade away, yeah?

95
00:09:45,339 --> 00:09:49,292
If it's on the dark side, you don't go so down with it.

96
00:09:49,412 --> 00:09:50,797
It doesn't depress you so much.

97
00:09:50,836 --> 00:09:55,451
You can keep aloof, you see?

98
00:10:00,982 --> 00:10:13,245
So these sort of reactions that we have of being happy and sad, delighted, despair, disappointed, gratified, expecting, fear, expectation, fear.

99
00:10:13,888 --> 00:10:18,296
All that, you see, begins to, although it's there, you're not getting caught up in it.

100
00:10:18,336 --> 00:10:19,818
There's a sort of evenness.

101
00:10:19,798 --> 00:10:23,466
Because you're not getting caught up in it, it's not developing.

102
00:10:23,908 --> 00:10:31,985
So these things are always going to happen to us, but our position now is that we don't get conned by them, don't get hijacked, you see.

103
00:10:34,024 --> 00:10:51,735
And the other thing about equanimity is because of that ability to be open, to be aware of these little things that are going on in our minds, the subliminal things, it helps us not to fall into the subtle enemies of love, compassion and joy.

104
00:10:52,596 --> 00:10:58,226
So you see attachment, you can see where the attachment is manifesting.

105
00:10:59,168 --> 00:11:01,650
But if you're caught up in it, you don't see it.

106
00:11:01,691 --> 00:11:08,779
You just find yourself behaving in a way which is using the other person.

107
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:10,201
I mean, that's what attachment is.

108
00:11:11,823 --> 00:11:14,326
And the same with compassion.

109
00:11:14,466 --> 00:11:18,432
So compassion is, you know, the subtle enemy is grief.

110
00:11:18,452 --> 00:11:21,035
You feel pity for, you feel sorry for somebody.

111
00:11:21,897 --> 00:11:22,798
That's not necessary.

112
00:11:22,817 --> 00:11:25,902
It's coming from a rather conceited place, actually.

113
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:29,173
Compassion is just the desire to help.

114
00:11:29,936 --> 00:11:34,208
But it doesn't mean to say that you can't feel the other person's pain.

115
00:11:36,777 --> 00:11:40,870
You can contact the other person's sorrow, but you don't have to feel sorry for them.

116
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:44,740
You can actually be with somebody who's in a...

117
00:11:45,140 --> 00:12:05,355
I remember at the funeral of my aunt, years and years and years ago, and I was with my cousin, we were about 18 or something, and we went off to another part of the seminary, sat on the bench together, and he just wept his eyes out, and I could, you know, I just felt, I could feel his pain, you see, I could feel it in my heart, I remember feeling it, you see, but I never felt sorry for him.

118
00:12:07,427 --> 00:12:12,635
Funny enough, I don't know why, I just thought actually I was happy for him because it seemed to get it off his chest, you see.

119
00:12:14,298 --> 00:12:15,279
And the same with joy.

120
00:12:16,621 --> 00:12:22,551
Joy slips into this sort of over-excitedness, you know, where you're really trying to just make yourself joyful.

121
00:12:24,453 --> 00:12:26,035
Trying to get the best out of your ice cream.

122
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:33,908
So what equanimity does, it just keeps that on an even keel, you see.

123
00:12:34,394 --> 00:12:44,227
And one begins to appreciate these beautiful states of mind in their more pure states.

124
00:12:44,288 --> 00:12:48,934
They don't get frazzled by these other little parts.

125
00:12:48,955 --> 00:12:52,419
So all in all, this equanimity is quite important.

126
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:53,542
Important to develop.

127
00:12:54,823 --> 00:13:06,279
It's important in the sense that we begin from when we're equanimous, even-minded, when we're still like that, we can see very clearly, much more clearly what's going on, what's going on around us, what's going on inside us.

128
00:13:08,102 --> 00:13:13,610
And that allows us to be more in control of our lives, you see.

129
00:13:14,873 --> 00:13:16,315
Hopefully leading to greater happiness.

130
00:13:21,947 --> 00:13:25,514
I can only hope my words have been of some assistance.

131
00:13:25,533 --> 00:13:39,417
May you be liberated from all your suffering, especially from any lack of equanimity, sooner rather than later.

